embeds.title: Jeremiah's Banner
embeds.description:
Uncommon Relic / The Slime Boss / Downfall

At the start of combat, **Split** into a **Leeching** Slime and gain 1 Slime slot.
*You and ooze army.*

messages.content: getting a slime into an open slot before the combat even begins has a lot of potential
with the right cards, you can take advantage of slime synergies without having to draw split cards first, although that's not always an issue
it being a blocking slime is great with Command to save you HP on turn 1
and you can use things like <slime tap> in a similar way to Fission, drawing you through your cards really quickly to get your deck going faster

I really like this relic, but I do have a tendency to go for slime summoning builds pretty frequently. As one of the very few ways to get more slime slots, it goes really well with sources of potency. Leeching slime is also one of the more valuable slimes, being a nice consistent source of block. I can't remember if Jeremiah's banner has a mini anchor effect (Does the summoned slime get to attack on turn 1 and give you block?)  The block consistency alone makes this a relic I will often buy from the shop if I see it, I find that slime boss deals damage very well, but can have some trouble with finding enough sources of mitigation.
